If you can, there are some really cool things that are in southern oregon that may be reasonable to hit on your way to crater lake. First, in Winston, there is a drive through and walk through zoo called Wildlife Safari. It is pretty cool if you like that kind of stuff. Second, the Oregon Caves farther south are a really cool stop as well. It is a nice stop and you can check out and take a tour deep into some really cool caves. Third (time permitting), Hells Gate jet boating excursions up the Rogue River. You can do half day or full day trips that are pretty fun, especially if you get a fun boat captain and a fun people on the boat with you. Oregon is a pretty cool place. There are quite a few destinations not too far of of I-5 that are pretty dang cool. Have fun, relax, and enjoy our delicious microbrews!
And most of these stops are just off or I-5 if you end up coming down that way instead of the coast route.

WRITING.TITLE: Apparently I was sent to collections..
WRITING.TEXT: So, my wife and I rented a house for about a year and a half. We had our power through Pacific Power. We moved out in June because we found someone to take over the lease, and they did so in July. Well I guess we either forgot to pay the final bill, or thought we had paid it, but actually didn't. I don't know. Whatever the case we are sitting here right now looking at our credit karma and it says my wife was sent to collections a couple days ago.. We logged into Pacific power and it said they sent the last email in August stating we had a bill of $120 and some change. We never received any other type of correspondence, no other bills or calls or anything saying that we are past due or are about to be sent to collections since then. We have also not recieved any notification yet that we are in collections.. What should I do now? Do I call Pacific power and try to talk to them? Do I just call the debt collector? I don't know. Any help would be greatly appreciated.

Thanks for the responses, I really appreciate it. We just spoke to Pacific Power and they have sold it to a collection agency about 2 hours south of us. We just tried calling them, but they are closed until Monday, so we will be trying again then. The lady from Pacific power said that the "should" remove it from my credit once it is paid.. I will make sure to get all that in writing, obviously.
